{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"mathsize","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Global_attributes/mathsize","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"\n    <ol>\n        <li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element\">MathML Reference</a></strong>\n\n        \n            </li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/maction\">&lt;maction&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/math\">&lt;math&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/menclose\">&lt;menclose&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/merror\">&lt;merror&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mfenced\">&lt;mfenced&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mfrac\">&lt;mfrac&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mi\">&lt;mi&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mmultiscripts\">&lt;mmultiscripts&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mn\">&lt;mn&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mo\">&lt;mo&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mover\">&lt;mover&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mpadded\">&lt;mpadded&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mphantom\">&lt;mphantom&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mroot\">&lt;mroot&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mrow\">&lt;mrow&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/ms\">&lt;ms&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mspace\">&lt;mspace&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/msqrt\">&lt;msqrt&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mstyle\">&lt;mstyle&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/msub\">&lt;msub&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/msubsup\">&lt;msubsup&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/msup\">&lt;msup&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mtable\">&lt;mtable&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mtd\">&lt;mtd&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mtext\">&lt;mtext&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mtr\">&lt;mtr&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/munder\">&lt;munder&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/munderover\">&lt;munderover&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/semantics\">&lt;semantics&gt;</a></li>\n        \n\n        \n    </ol>\n","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard deprecated\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Deprecated:</strong> This feature is no longer recommended. Though some browsers might still support it, it may have already been removed from the relevant web standards, may be in the process of being dropped, or may only be kept for compatibility purposes. Avoid using it, and update existing code if possible; see the <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">compatibility table</a> at the bottom of this page to guide your decision. Be aware that this feature may cease to work at any time.</p></div>\n<p>The <strong><code>mathsize</code></strong> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Global_attributes\">global attribute</a> sets the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/font-size\">font-size</a> of a MathML element.</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect2\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> Use CSS for styling MathML whenever possible. The <code>mathsize</code> attribute should only be included for applications that are not CSS-aware and will be overridden by the CSS <code>font-size</code> property, if set.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- &lt;length&gt; values --&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>math</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">mathsize</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>12px<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>math</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">mathsize</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>0.8em<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- &lt;percentage&gt; values --&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>math</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">mathsize</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>80%<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"values","title":"Values","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"length\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length\"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>A positive <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length\"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a> value. For most font-relative units (such as <code>em</code> and <code>ex</code>), the font size is relative to the parent element's font size.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"percentage\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/percentage\"><code>&lt;percentage&gt;</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>A positive <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/percentage\"><code>&lt;percentage&gt;</code></a> value, relative to the parent element's font size.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"query":"mathml.global_attributes.mathsize","specifications":[]}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>\n    In MathML 3 and earlier versions, keywords <code>small</code>, <code>normal</code>, and <code>big</code> as\n    well as the MathML3-specific syntax for lengths was supported.\n    Since MathML Core, the syntax matches CSS\n    <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length-percentage\"><code>&lt;length-percentage&gt;</code></a> values.\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    This attribute was designed for MathML applications that are not CSS-aware.\n    Since MathML Core, the use of equivalent CSS is recommended instead.\n  </li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"data":null,"query":"mathml.global_attributes.mathsize","browsers":null}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>All <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Global_attributes\">global attributes</a>.</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/font-size\"><code>font-size</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The mathsize global attribute sets the font-size of a MathML element.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-20T02:49:59.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/mathml/global_attributes/mathsize","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/mathml/global_attributes/mathsize/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/309b7e313af4aebde03f5825ec530db614e2bb16","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML","title":"MathML"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Global_attributes","title":"Global attributes"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Global_attributes/mathsize","title":"mathsize"}],"pageTitle":"mathsize - MathML | MDN","noIndexing":false}}